So, I was just editing a module and ran into something pretty interesting.  Wondering if someone can shed some insight on it.

Within this module, I've got two field groups which I have labeled `appearance` and `content`.  Now when I edit the module at the page level, I'm seeing something I've never seen before.  The `content` field group is collapsed and when I click it, it takes me into a new pane (similar to editing a repeating field).

As I said before, I've never seen this before... but I really really like it.  How do I get all my field groups to show up collapsed like this?
I really like this UI with the content being opened in a new pane. How can I make this work for other modules? This can really help remove some clutter
Figured it out.  It's due to nesting field groups
Now we just need two naming conventions for each section lol
lol
I'm guessing you could probably name the nested one Appearance as well

Wow.  You can actually just group two fields within your field group and then move them back out so you just have an empty field group, you get the same effect and it doesn't show up in the page editor
